{
    "name": "REAL-PE: ISTH Major Bleed — Diagnosis Code Component",
    "description": "Outcome sub-cohort capturing the diagnosis-code arm of the ISTH major-bleed definition (Schulman 2005). This cohort alone is NOT the full ISTH outcome — the complete ISTH definition is: (bleed diagnosis code within 7d post-index) OR (blood transfusion within 7d AND Hgb drop >=2 g/dL). The transfusion-plus-lab arm is assembled in sql/02_isth_barc_outcomes.sql because standard Circe cannot join MEASUREMENT to PROCEDURE_OCCURRENCE with value-based thresholds. Use this cohort for the diagnosis-code leg only; the SQL template references it by cohort_definition_id.",
